1
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,074
Delicious Vegan Sausages, Cheese
and Burgers - Vegusto.co.uk

2
00:00:15,915 --> 00:00:19,367
Man:
SO THE HOUSE HAS
A REALLY WONDERFUL FLOW.

3
00:00:19,368 --> 00:00:21,186
IT'S PERFECT
FOR ENTERTAINING

4
00:00:21,187 --> 00:00:24,423
OR ENJOYING AN
INDOOR-OUTDOOR LIFESTYLE.

5
00:00:24,424 --> 00:00:27,926
YOU SEE HOW EACH OF
THE ROOMS IS CONNECTED?
IT'S GREAT, ISN'T IT?

6
00:00:27,927 --> 00:00:31,346
THE KITCHEN HAS ALL
THE MODERN APPLIANCES.

7
00:00:31,347 --> 00:00:34,649
AND RIGHT THROUGH HERE,
THERE'S A SMALLER BEDROOM.

8
00:00:40,106 --> 00:00:41,957
IT'S PERFECT FOR CHILDREN.

9
00:00:47,363 --> 00:00:49,631
IT'S PEACEFUL
OUT HERE, ISN'T IT?

10
00:00:49,632 --> 00:00:51,866
Woman:
GARDEN LOOKS LIKE
IT'S A LOT OF WORK.

11
00:00:51,867 --> 00:00:55,420
ACTUALLY, YOU'D BE
SURPRISED HOW WELL
IT MAINTAINS ITSELF.

12
00:00:55,421 --> 00:00:58,423
Man:
THE ROOF LOOKS KINDA OLD.

13
00:00:58,424 --> 00:01:00,391
Realtor:
HAVE YOU SEEN
THE KITCHEN YET?

14
00:01:00,392 --> 00:01:01,976
THE MARBLE'S WONDERFUL.

15
00:01:05,098 --> 00:01:06,831
(chain clicks)

16
00:01:17,560 --> 00:01:20,695
- THANKS VERY MUCH.
- OH. THANKS FOR
STOPPING BY.

17
00:01:20,696 --> 00:01:23,197
- DID I GIVE YOU MY CARD?
- YES.  WE'LL BE IN TOUCH.

18
00:01:23,198 --> 00:01:26,468
- ALL RIGHT.
THANKS AGAIN.
- THANK YOU.

19
00:01:26,469 --> 00:01:29,136
BYE NOW.

20
00:01:54,379 --> 00:01:56,114
HELLO?

21
00:02:21,073 --> 00:02:23,124
(panting)

22
00:02:38,574 --> 00:02:41,493
- Woman: HELLO? CARL?
- HEY.  ALICE.

23
00:02:41,494 --> 00:02:43,427
I'M DOWN HERE.

24
00:02:43,428 --> 00:02:45,062
IS IT HOT OUT?

25
00:02:48,751 --> 00:02:51,936
- HOW'D IT GO?
- UH, IT WENT OKAY.

26
00:02:53,839 --> 00:02:56,774
- THAT BAD, HUH?
- IT'S A TOUGH MARKET.

27
00:02:56,775 --> 00:03:00,845
WE COULD WAIT A FEW MONTHS,
SEE IF THINGS TURN AROUND.

28
00:03:05,551 --> 00:03:08,619
LOOK, I KNOW YOU
HAD DIFFERENT PLANS
FOR THE HOUSE.

29
00:03:10,939 --> 00:03:12,607
IT'S OKAY.

30
00:03:14,209 --> 00:03:15,693
- Alice: I'M SORRY.
- (chuckles)

31
00:03:17,163 --> 00:03:19,698
YOU KNOW, I'M ALWAYS
HERE FOR YOU, ALICE,

32
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:22,717
IF YOU EVER--
IF YOU EVER WANNA TALK.

33
00:03:22,718 --> 00:03:24,852
THANKS, CARL.

34
00:03:27,506 --> 00:03:29,173
- BYE.
- BYE. YEAH.

35
00:03:38,851 --> 00:03:41,603
(shower running)

36
00:04:15,871 --> 00:04:18,339
Alice on film:
Honey, what do you think
of this room

37
00:04:18,340 --> 00:04:21,141
for a new nursery?

38
00:04:23,362 --> 00:04:25,663
Man on film:
I think we could fit
a pool table in here.

39
00:04:25,664 --> 00:04:27,665
Alice on film:
Josh, you're a dork.

40
00:04:34,089 --> 00:04:35,373
- (both chuckling)
- Alice: Oh God.

41
00:04:35,374 --> 00:04:37,525
(remote clicks)

42
00:04:41,963 --> 00:04:44,899
(glasses clinking)

43
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:48,319
- SO THE CAR WAS TOTALED.
- YOU MEAN MY CAR
WAS TOTALED.

44
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:49,954
WELL, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU LET OSCAR

45
00:04:49,955 --> 00:04:51,422
DRIVE YOUR CAR
IN THE SNOW.

46
00:04:51,423 --> 00:04:53,091
Man:
UH-UH. I WAS NOT DRIVING.

47
00:04:53,092 --> 00:04:54,959
SO WHO WAS DRIVING?
WALTER?

48
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:57,395
- OSCAR.  OSCAR.
- (all laugh)

49
00:04:57,396 --> 00:05:00,882
- OSCAR, WHEN'S HE BACK
FROM BERLIN?
- TWO WEEKS.

50
00:05:00,883 --> 00:05:03,685
HEY, IS THERE
ANY MORE OF THIS WINE?

51
00:05:03,686 --> 00:05:05,553
YEAH.

52
00:05:08,624 --> 00:05:10,024
YOU'RE DOING GREAT.

53
00:05:10,025 --> 00:05:13,077
YOU TALKED
TO HIM RECENTLY?

54
00:05:13,078 --> 00:05:16,280
NOT REALLY.
I MEAN, I TOLD HIM
I WAS SELLING THE HOUSE.

55
00:05:16,281 --> 00:05:18,115
GOOD.

56
00:05:18,116 --> 00:05:20,001
HE SAID I WAS
BEING IRRATIONAL.

57
00:05:20,002 --> 00:05:24,622
ACTUALLY, WHAT HE SAID
WAS "OVERLY EMOTIONAL."
HIS FAVORITE.

58
00:05:24,623 --> 00:05:27,441
WELL, THEN YOU CAN TELL HIM
HE CAN KEEP PAYING HIS
HALF OF THE MORTGAGE.

59
00:05:27,442 --> 00:05:31,780
I MEAN, SERIOUSLY?
SCREW HIM. IS HE REALLY
THAT OUT OF TOUCH?

60
00:05:31,781 --> 00:05:34,149
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE IT'S A GOOD THING.

61
00:05:34,150 --> 00:05:36,284
YOU KNOW?
A GOOD CLEAN BREAK.

62
00:05:36,285 --> 00:05:38,219
THAT WHAT YOUR
THERAPIST SAID?

63
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:40,155
I DON'T KNOW.
I CAN'T AFFORD HER ANYMORE.

64
00:05:52,868 --> 00:05:54,969
GOD, YOU ARE SUCH
A LIGHTWEIGHT.

65
00:05:54,970 --> 00:05:58,006
I KNOW IT'S, LIKE,
ONLY A COUPLE DATES,

66
00:05:58,007 --> 00:06:00,308
BUT I REALLY THINK
HE MIGHT BE THE ONE.

67
00:06:02,878 --> 00:06:05,146
- ALICE, ARE YOU EVEN AWAKE?
- YEAH, I'M AWAKE.

68
00:06:05,147 --> 00:06:07,314
(laughs)
WHAT DID I JUST SAY?

69
00:06:07,315 --> 00:06:09,233
YOU HAVE A REALLY GOOD
FEELING ABOUT HIM.

70
00:06:16,575 --> 00:06:18,509
(crickets chirping)

71
00:06:34,093 --> 00:06:36,878
JENNIE?

72
00:06:47,239 --> 00:06:48,889
JENN, YOU UP HERE?

73
00:06:52,794 --> 00:06:54,612
JENN.

74
00:07:01,286 --> 00:07:03,270
JENN?

75
00:07:24,025 --> 00:07:26,594
(door opens, creaks)

76
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:30,214
(water running)

77
00:08:08,136 --> 00:08:09,821
JENNIE, WHERE ARE YOU?

78
00:08:27,355 --> 00:08:29,257
JENNIE?

79
00:08:33,111 --> 00:08:35,997
JENNIE, ARE YOU THERE?

80
00:08:35,998 --> 00:08:37,965
THIS BETTER NOT
BE A JOKE.

81
00:08:40,452 --> 00:08:43,087
(creaks)

82
00:08:45,490 --> 00:08:47,341
JENN?

83
00:08:50,679 --> 00:08:52,697
JENNIE, ARE YOU THERE?

84
00:08:58,103 --> 00:09:00,271
JENNIE?

85
00:09:04,843 --> 00:09:07,478
JENNIE?

86
00:09:08,580 --> 00:09:10,515
(shrieking)

87
00:09:20,025 --> 00:09:21,959
(thudding footsteps)

88
00:09:28,450 --> 00:09:30,551
(murmurs)

89
00:09:41,279 --> 00:09:43,597
(muffled panting)

90
00:09:49,488 --> 00:09:51,706
(door opens, creaks)

91
00:09:54,276 --> 00:09:56,343
(latches clicking)

92
00:09:58,046 --> 00:09:59,981
(muffled whimpering,
protesting)

93
00:10:01,149 --> 00:10:04,352
(muffled)
NO NO NO!

94
00:10:53,902 --> 00:10:56,670
VERY NICE.

95
00:11:03,011 --> 00:11:05,146
I LOVE THE MARBLE.

96
00:11:29,787 --> 00:11:32,123
I LOVE IT.
IT'S HOME.

97
00:11:35,544 --> 00:11:37,728
(ringing)

98
00:11:37,729 --> 00:11:41,798
HI, ALICE, IT'S ME.
I'M GONNA SWING BY
AND PICK UP MY GOLF CLUBS.

99
00:11:41,799 --> 00:11:44,501
I THOUGHT
I COULD HAVE A LOOK
AT THE HOT TUB FOR YOU.

100
00:11:44,502 --> 00:11:47,171
ARE YOU THERE?
I'M IN HOLLYWOOD

101
00:11:47,172 --> 00:11:50,007
SO I'M GONNA BE BY
PRETTY SOON.

102
00:11:50,008 --> 00:11:51,776
(beeps)

103
00:12:07,909 --> 00:12:09,593
ALICE?

104
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:15,115
ANYONE HOME?

105
00:12:33,385 --> 00:12:35,519
HI THERE.

106
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:37,504
HELLO.

107
00:12:37,505 --> 00:12:40,724
I'M JOSH.
I'M ALICE'S EX.

108
00:12:40,725 --> 00:12:43,610
I'M LILA.
I'M JUST VISITING.

109
00:12:46,131 --> 00:12:47,899
DO YOU KNOW
IF ALICE IS HOME?

110
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:50,801
ALICE? NO.
NO, SHE'S NOT IN.

111
00:12:50,802 --> 00:12:54,322
SHE ASKED ME TO CHECK
THE TIMER ON THE HOT TUB.

112
00:12:54,323 --> 00:12:56,707
BY ALL MEANS.

113
00:13:00,679 --> 00:13:03,280
- HOW'S THE TEMPERATURE?
- IT'S PERFECT.

114
00:13:03,281 --> 00:13:04,982
GREAT.

115
00:13:09,053 --> 00:13:14,075
SO, UM, HOW LONG ARE YOU
GONNA BE IN TOWN FOR?

116
00:13:14,076 --> 00:13:16,543
JUST A FEW DAYS.

117
00:13:16,544 --> 00:13:19,313
I DON'T KNOW,
MAYBE LONGER.

118
00:13:19,314 --> 00:13:20,664
REALLY, IT ALL DEPENDS.

119
00:13:22,067 --> 00:13:25,119
WOULD YOU BE A DARLING
AND FILL MY GLASS?

120
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:27,355
THE BOTTLE'S ON THE TABLE.

121
00:13:27,356 --> 00:13:29,090
SURE.

122
00:13:40,068 --> 00:13:43,738
- YOU WANT A GLASS?
- I SHOULD PROBABLY
GET GOING.

123
00:13:45,506 --> 00:13:47,708
WHY? YOU GOT TO
RUSH OFF SOMEWHERE?

124
00:13:47,709 --> 00:13:51,462
NOT REALLY.
JUST GOT SOME ERRANDS.

125
00:13:53,031 --> 00:13:54,565
I SEE.

126
00:13:56,801 --> 00:14:00,637
IF YOU SEE ALICE,
COULD YOU TELL HER
I STOPPED BY?

127
00:14:00,638 --> 00:14:02,740
- OF COURSE.
- ALL RIGHT.

128
00:14:04,075 --> 00:14:06,177
NICE TO MEET YOU.

129
00:14:06,178 --> 00:14:09,430
JOSH, CAN I ASK YOU
A PERSONAL QUESTION?

130
00:14:11,166 --> 00:14:13,751
- I'M SORRY?
- I'M TRYING TO DECIDE

131
00:14:13,752 --> 00:14:16,653
IF I SHOULD TELL YOU
SOMETHING ABOUT ALICE.

132
00:14:16,654 --> 00:14:19,656
BUT FIRST I NEED TO ASK YOU
A PERSONAL QUESTION.

133
00:14:21,310 --> 00:14:22,976
OKAY.

134
00:14:24,946 --> 00:14:28,165
WHAT ARE YOUR TRUE
FEELINGS FOR HER?

135
00:14:28,166 --> 00:14:31,969
- MY TRUE FEELINGS?
- ARE YOU STILL IN
LOVE WITH HER?

136
00:14:31,970 --> 00:14:35,139
WELL, OBVIOUSLY,
I STILL CARE FOR ALICE.

137
00:14:35,140 --> 00:14:37,308
- OKAY.
- BUT I--

138
00:14:37,309 --> 00:14:39,510
I DON'T THINK I'M
IN LOVE WITH HER ANYMORE.

139
00:14:39,511 --> 00:14:41,562
WHAT HAPPENED?

140
00:14:41,563 --> 00:14:44,915
OH, I DON'T KNOW.
IT FADED, I GUESS.

141
00:14:46,501 --> 00:14:48,435
THAT'S WHY WE'RE APART.

142
00:14:48,436 --> 00:14:53,573
UM, SO WHAT WAS
THIS INFORMATION?

143
00:14:55,477 --> 00:14:58,662
COME ON.  HAVE SOME WINE.
ONE GLASS WON'T KILL YOU.

144
00:15:01,616 --> 00:15:03,350
GO ON THEN.

145
00:15:14,045 --> 00:15:17,214
SO WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO TELL ME?

146
00:15:17,215 --> 00:15:19,383
YOU'RE ALL BUSINESS,
AREN'T YOU, JOSH?

147
00:15:19,384 --> 00:15:23,220
NO. I JUST HAVE THE FEELING
THAT YOU'RE TOTALLY
MESSING WITH ME.

148
00:15:23,221 --> 00:15:25,522
WHAT IF I AM?

149
00:15:28,342 --> 00:15:31,078
- HAVE YOU MET ANYONE NEW?
- NO.

150
00:15:31,079 --> 00:15:33,864
UM, NOT SERIOUS ANYWAY.

151
00:15:35,016 --> 00:15:37,718
WHY? HAS ALICE?
IS THAT IT?

152
00:15:37,719 --> 00:15:39,953
NO. MAYBE.

153
00:15:41,823 --> 00:15:43,740
I CAN'T BE SURE.

154
00:15:43,741 --> 00:15:46,660
WHAT ABOUT YOU?
ARE YOU WITH ANYONE?

155
00:15:46,661 --> 00:15:49,163
THERE IS SOMEONE.

156
00:15:49,164 --> 00:15:51,365
HOW DO YOU MAKE IT WORK?

157
00:15:51,366 --> 00:15:54,334
WE HAVE AN
OPEN RELATIONSHIP.

158
00:15:54,335 --> 00:15:56,670
REALLY?

159
00:15:56,671 --> 00:15:59,206
- MM-HMM.
- AND YOU'RE
COOL WITH THAT?

160
00:15:59,207 --> 00:16:00,624
I THINK SO.

161
00:16:00,625 --> 00:16:02,659
(chuckles)

162
00:16:02,660 --> 00:16:05,196
IT'S A LITTLE
FRIGHTENING AT FIRST

163
00:16:05,197 --> 00:16:08,499
WHEN YOU REALIZE YOU HAVE
OTHER DESIRES, YOU KNOW?

164
00:16:10,568 --> 00:16:12,503
HOW DO YOU ADMIT
SOMETHING LIKE THAT

165
00:16:12,504 --> 00:16:14,605
TO THE PERSON
THAT MOST COMPLETES YOU?

166
00:16:14,606 --> 00:16:17,958
BUT IF YOU CROSS
THE LINE TOGETHER

167
00:16:17,959 --> 00:16:20,294
AND YOU'RE HONEST
WITH EACH OTHER,

168
00:16:20,295 --> 00:16:23,713
IT CAN BRING YOU CLOSER.

169
00:16:25,717 --> 00:16:27,284
YOU TELL HIM EVERYTHING?

170
00:16:27,285 --> 00:16:28,819
THAT'S PART OF THE DEAL.

171
00:16:28,820 --> 00:16:32,206
WHAT ABOUT HIM?
DO YOU BELIEVE HE
TELLS YOU EVERYTHING?

172
00:16:32,207 --> 00:16:33,924
OF COURSE.

173
00:16:40,865 --> 00:16:43,550
(inaudible conversation)

174
00:16:47,388 --> 00:16:50,140
...NOT GUILTY.

175
00:16:50,141 --> 00:16:52,593
- DO YOU FEEL GUILTY
ABOUT SOMETHING?
- NO.

176
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:54,595
NOR DO I.

177
00:16:54,596 --> 00:16:59,016
YOU REALLY--
YOU ARE QUITE SOMETHING.

178
00:17:03,421 --> 00:17:06,440
WHAT WAS THE--
WHAT DID YOU WANT
TO TELL ME?

179
00:17:06,441 --> 00:17:08,626
OKAY, I'LL TELL YOU
ON ONE CONDITION--

180
00:17:09,794 --> 00:17:12,696
YOU HAVE TO GET
IN THE WATER.

181
00:17:12,697 --> 00:17:14,765
NO WAY.  NO.
I CAN'T DO THAT.

182
00:17:14,766 --> 00:17:17,134
WHAT IF ALICE
GETS BACK AND SEES ME?
SHE'LL KILL ME.

183
00:17:17,135 --> 00:17:19,069
SHE'S NOT GONNA
BE BACK ANYTIME SOON.

184
00:17:20,922 --> 00:17:24,558
DIDN'T SHE TELL YOU?
I'M HOUSESITTING.

185
00:17:24,559 --> 00:17:26,360
SO?

186
00:17:28,246 --> 00:17:32,432
LOOK.
NOW YOU'RE ALL WET.

187
00:17:32,433 --> 00:17:35,302
NOW YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO COME IN.

188
00:17:48,867 --> 00:17:50,901
(thudding footsteps)

189
00:17:50,902 --> 00:17:52,870
(inhales weakly)

190
00:18:07,802 --> 00:18:10,804
- MAYBE WE SHOULDN'T.
- THEN STOP.

191
00:18:30,575 --> 00:18:32,509
(panting, moaning)

192
00:18:43,588 --> 00:18:46,190
(cries out)

193
00:19:11,866 --> 00:19:13,500
(whimpers faintly)

194
00:19:14,769 --> 00:19:17,804
Lila: DAVID?

195
00:19:47,268 --> 00:19:49,202
(saw buzzing faintly)

196
00:19:59,063 --> 00:20:00,764
IT'S SO QUIET HERE.

197
00:20:00,765 --> 00:20:03,600
I CAN'T WAIT TO MEET
THE NEIGHBORS.

198
00:20:04,952 --> 00:20:06,887
(fork clinks)

199
00:20:10,275 --> 00:20:12,743
IT WAS FUN TODAY,
WASN'T IT?

200
00:20:17,064 --> 00:20:20,800
AFTER DINNER, WILL YOU
SET UP THE VIDEO?

201
00:20:35,083 --> 00:20:36,766
- (grunts softly)
- (chains jingle)

202
00:20:46,294 --> 00:20:48,095
HMM.

203
00:21:01,876 --> 00:21:03,577
SHE HAD GOOD TASTE.

204
00:21:20,961 --> 00:21:24,665
YOU KNOW, IT'S ACTUALLY
BEEN A PRETTY LONG DAY.

205
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:34,157
DAVID.

206
00:21:36,944 --> 00:21:38,812
YOU'RE HAPPY
I'M BACK, RIGHT?

207
00:21:45,987 --> 00:21:49,339
GOOD NIGHT, DAVID.

208
00:21:49,340 --> 00:21:50,957
GOOD NIGHT, LILA.

209
00:22:02,169 --> 00:22:03,687
(clicks)

210
00:22:03,688 --> 00:22:06,390
(Josh speaking
on film)

211
00:22:06,391 --> 00:22:09,726
(loud rustling
on film)

212
00:22:12,630 --> 00:22:14,164
Don't lock us in.

213
00:22:14,165 --> 00:22:16,199
Obviously.

214
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:18,101
(kissing on film)

215
00:22:20,104 --> 00:22:22,072
(mumbles)

216
00:22:26,561 --> 00:22:28,678
It's pretty hard
to do.

217
00:22:28,679 --> 00:22:31,347
(giggles)
You're very talented.

218
00:22:35,703 --> 00:22:38,539
- Cheers to?
- To...

219
00:22:38,540 --> 00:22:40,574
our new home.

220
00:22:43,494 --> 00:22:44,811
(clicks)

221
00:22:57,758 --> 00:22:59,559
- (footsteps)
- Lila: BYE.

222
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:01,227
SEE YOU TONIGHT.

223
00:23:18,796 --> 00:23:20,096
(knife slides free)

224
00:23:26,236 --> 00:23:28,337
(creaks)

225
00:23:45,172 --> 00:23:47,473
(chains jangling)

226
00:23:50,210 --> 00:23:53,446
(Alice whimpering)

227
00:24:01,422 --> 00:24:04,157
(gasping)

228
00:24:05,559 --> 00:24:07,527
(breathlessly)
I DON'T WANT TO DIE.

229
00:24:08,596 --> 00:24:11,581
PLEASE.
I HAVE MONEY.

230
00:24:15,203 --> 00:24:17,170
(screaming)
HELP ME, PLEASE!

231
00:24:23,261 --> 00:24:26,596
(shrieks)
HELP! SOMEBODY HELP!

232
00:24:29,066 --> 00:24:30,851
NO ONE CAN HEAR YOU.

233
00:24:34,889 --> 00:24:37,206
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

234
00:24:41,812 --> 00:24:43,746
(chains jangling)

235
00:24:56,344 --> 00:24:57,995
HERE.

236
00:24:59,246 --> 00:25:01,331
DRINK.

237
00:25:05,203 --> 00:25:08,205
IF SHE FINDS OUT
YOU'RE ALIVE,
YOU'LL DIE.

238
00:25:10,642 --> 00:25:12,559
OKAY.

239
00:25:12,560 --> 00:25:14,761
I HAVE TO WORK.

240
00:25:25,823 --> 00:25:27,874
WOULD YOU LIKE
SOMETHING TO READ?

