(Alice shivering)

491
00:51:17,740 --> 00:51:19,874
(coughs wetly)

492
00:51:19,875 --> 00:51:22,261
HE'S NOT DEAD.

493
00:51:22,262 --> 00:51:23,828
I CUT HIS ARTERY.
HE WILL BE.

494
00:51:29,135 --> 00:51:31,085
- LILA.
- YES?

495
00:51:32,388 --> 00:51:34,273
WHAT?

496
00:51:34,274 --> 00:51:37,576
NOTHING.

497
00:51:37,577 --> 00:51:39,545
I'M GONNA USE
THE OTHER SHOWER.

498
00:51:48,153 --> 00:51:51,089
I THINK I'D LIKE TO THROW
A DINNER PARTY.

499
00:51:51,090 --> 00:51:52,724
REALLY?

500
00:51:52,725 --> 00:51:54,759
WHAT, YOU DON'T
THINK WE SHOULD?

501
00:51:54,760 --> 00:52:00,282
I WAS JUST--
WE BARELY SPEND
ANY TIME HERE JUST US.

502
00:52:00,283 --> 00:52:02,767
WE'LL HAVE TO BE
ON THE MOVE SOON ANYWAY.

503
00:52:02,768 --> 00:52:05,153
- (phone rings)
- (answering machine beeps)

504
00:52:05,154 --> 00:52:07,722
Hey, it's Oscar.
I'm just checking up on you.

505
00:52:07,723 --> 00:52:09,758
We got the message
from your doctor.

506
00:52:09,759 --> 00:52:11,877
Hope you got your voice back
and you're feeling better.

507
00:52:11,878 --> 00:52:16,198
Anyway, in case you were
wondering, the office is
so boring without you.

508
00:52:16,199 --> 00:52:18,383
Call me, okay?
I want to know you're okay.

509
00:52:18,384 --> 00:52:20,352
Just call me.
Love you.  Bye.

510
00:52:22,455 --> 00:52:24,489
WHAT ABOUT TOMORROW NIGHT?

511
00:52:24,490 --> 00:52:26,358
TOMORROW?

512
00:52:26,359 --> 00:52:29,044
WHAT, YOU HAVE OTHER PLANS?

513
00:52:34,333 --> 00:52:36,518
I WONDER
WHAT I SHOULD WEAR.

514
00:53:18,761 --> 00:53:20,845
(latch clicks)

515
00:53:27,670 --> 00:53:29,521
ALICE.

516
00:53:32,775 --> 00:53:34,276
(whispers)
ALICE.

517
00:53:40,816 --> 00:53:43,334
HERE'S A BLANKET.

518
00:53:45,637 --> 00:53:47,221
Alice:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

519
00:53:47,222 --> 00:53:50,275
IT'S OKAY.
SHE'S ASLEEP.

520
00:54:18,371 --> 00:54:21,339
HERE.
THIS'LL KEEP YOU WARM.

521
00:54:31,450 --> 00:54:34,986
I WANT TO STOP.

522
00:54:36,055 --> 00:54:38,122
REALLY?

523
00:54:38,123 --> 00:54:39,824
YEAH.

524
00:54:39,825 --> 00:54:43,394
THEN YOU'LL HAVE
TO LEAVE HER.

525
00:54:45,665 --> 00:54:47,365
I KNOW.

526
00:54:49,134 --> 00:54:51,469
IT'LL BE OKAY.

527
00:55:04,851 --> 00:55:06,918
WILL YOU COME
WITH ME?

528
00:55:10,823 --> 00:55:12,491
YEAH.

529
00:55:12,492 --> 00:55:14,125
I'LL COME WITH YOU.

530
00:55:15,745 --> 00:55:17,245
- (door opens, creaks)
- Lila: DAVID?

531
00:55:17,246 --> 00:55:19,281
(both gasp)

532
00:55:23,886 --> 00:55:25,804
DAVID.

533
00:55:47,693 --> 00:55:49,277
(door closes)

534
00:56:03,359 --> 00:56:05,327
WHERE'D YOU GO?

535
00:56:05,328 --> 00:56:07,929
I WAS IN THE GARAGE.

536
00:56:07,930 --> 00:56:10,281
OH.

537
00:56:10,282 --> 00:56:12,451
I THOUGHT I HEARD YOU
TALKING TO SOMEONE.

538
00:56:12,452 --> 00:56:14,953
NO.

539
00:56:14,954 --> 00:56:17,388
I HAD TO CHECK ON
SOMETHING.

540
00:56:18,991 --> 00:56:20,842
WHAT?

541
00:56:20,843 --> 00:56:22,977
- ONE OF THE BODIES.
- OH.

542
00:56:27,883 --> 00:56:29,117
ARE THEY ROTTING?

543
00:56:30,786 --> 00:56:33,688
YEAH.
THEY'RE STARTING TO.

544
00:56:39,095 --> 00:56:40,328
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

545
00:56:42,064 --> 00:56:44,298
GOT LONELY UP THERE
ALL BY MYSELF.

546
00:56:47,269 --> 00:56:48,870
I COULDN'T FIND YOU.

547
00:56:48,871 --> 00:56:51,289
I'M SORRY.

548
00:56:55,745 --> 00:56:57,546
GOOD NIGHT, DAVID.

549
00:56:57,547 --> 00:56:59,714
GOOD NIGHT, LILA.

550
00:57:59,224 --> 00:58:03,011
(zipper zips)

551
00:58:34,643 --> 00:58:37,128
DAVID?

552
00:58:37,129 --> 00:58:40,348
DAVID!

553
00:59:05,107 --> 00:59:06,941
I THOUGHT YOU LEFT
WITHOUT ME.

554
00:59:20,839 --> 00:59:22,340
THANK YOU.

555
00:59:42,828 --> 00:59:45,996
DAVID, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

556
00:59:45,997 --> 00:59:48,399
PREPARING DINNER.

557
00:59:50,302 --> 00:59:52,137
YOU COULD HELP
IF YOU'D LIKE.

558
00:59:56,142 --> 00:59:59,444
DON'T DO THIS, OKAY?

559
01:00:02,230 --> 01:00:04,181
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO DO THIS.

560
01:00:09,154 --> 01:00:10,855
IT'S NOT TOO LATE
TO STOP.

561
01:00:16,262 --> 01:00:18,462
YOU HAVE TO
GO BACK DOWNSTAIRS.

562
01:00:21,466 --> 01:00:24,119
WHY?

563
01:00:27,372 --> 01:00:28,840
I KNOW YOU THINK
I'M DIFFERENT.

564
01:00:30,426 --> 01:00:31,992
BUT LILA'S PART OF ME.

565
01:00:34,730 --> 01:00:36,680
(phone ringing)

566
01:00:41,320 --> 01:00:43,621
Hey, Alice.
It's Oscar again.

567
01:00:43,622 --> 01:00:45,757
- I still haven't heard
from you. Are you okay?
- (scraping)

568
01:00:45,758 --> 01:00:47,676
I'm starting
to get really worried.

569
01:00:47,677 --> 01:00:49,260
Call me.

570
01:00:49,261 --> 01:00:51,196
(scraping continues)

571
01:00:59,187 --> 01:01:02,807
- DAVID, WHAT TIME IS IT?
- IT'S ALMOST 8:00.

572
01:01:02,808 --> 01:01:06,277
ARE THERE
ANY MORE CANDLES?
I THINK WE NEED MORE CANDLES.

573
01:01:06,278 --> 01:01:08,429
DO YOU THINK WE SHOULD
DECANT THE RED WINE?

574
01:01:11,016 --> 01:01:13,050
- WOULD YOU LIKE ME TO?
- MAYBE.

575
01:01:13,051 --> 01:01:15,486
I WANT EVERYTHING
TO BE PERFECT.

576
01:01:15,487 --> 01:01:17,839
- IT IS PERFECT.
- SO?

577
01:01:24,362 --> 01:01:26,164
- YOU LOOK GREAT.
- (giggles)

578
01:01:26,165 --> 01:01:28,449
WHAT ABOUT THE SHOES?
TOO MUCH?

579
01:01:28,450 --> 01:01:30,802
- THEY LOOK GOOD.
- THEY DO, DON'T THEY?

580
01:01:32,554 --> 01:01:35,055
HURRY UP AND CHANGE.
PEOPLE ARE GONNA BE
ARRIVING ANY MINUTE.

581
01:01:35,056 --> 01:01:36,858
I'M ALMOST DONE.

582
01:01:46,385 --> 01:01:49,304
- HI!
- HI!

583
01:01:49,305 --> 01:01:51,639
LILA, THIS IS
MY FIANCÉ SETH.

584
01:01:51,640 --> 01:01:54,926
- NICE TO MEET YOU.
- HI. HERE. WE BROUGHT
YOU SOME WINE.

585
01:01:54,927 --> 01:01:57,561
OH, THANK YOU.
THAT'S SO SWEET OF YOU.

586
01:01:57,562 --> 01:02:00,632
DAVID'S JUST UPSTAIRS.
HE'LL BE DOWN IN A SECOND.

587
01:02:00,633 --> 01:02:02,734
- I LOVE THIS HOUSE.
- OH, THANK YOU.

588
01:02:02,735 --> 01:02:04,802
WE'RE REALLY HAPPY HERE.

589
01:02:04,803 --> 01:02:06,354
PLEASE, COME ON IN.

590
01:02:06,355 --> 01:02:09,057
(footsteps)

591
01:02:17,599 --> 01:02:19,450
(mock laugh)

592
01:02:41,673 --> 01:02:43,941
THERE HE IS.

593
01:02:43,942 --> 01:02:46,461
DAVID, THIS IS
LAUREN AND SETH.

594
01:02:46,462 --> 01:02:48,362
- HI. HOW ARE YOU?
- HI. NICE TO MEET YOU.

595
01:02:48,363 --> 01:02:50,331
- HI.
- HI. WELCOME.

596
01:02:50,332 --> 01:02:53,367
THANK YOU.
AND THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR INVITING US.

597
01:02:53,368 --> 01:02:55,386
OF COURSE.
WE LOVE MEETING
NEW PEOPLE.

598
01:02:55,387 --> 01:02:58,873
DAVID, SETH AND LAUREN
JUST MOVED HERE
FROM SEATTLE.

599
01:02:58,874 --> 01:03:00,007
NO.
UH, SAN FRANCISCO.

600
01:03:00,008 --> 01:03:03,110
OH, RIGHT!
SAN FRANCISCO.
I'M SORRY.

601
01:03:03,111 --> 01:03:04,712
AND YOU'RE A DOCTOR.
IS THAT RIGHT?

602
01:03:04,713 --> 01:03:08,482
THAT'S RIGHT.
I JUST STARTED MY
RESIDENCY AT CEDARS-SINAI.

603
01:03:08,483 --> 01:03:10,017
SO HOW DID
YOU AND LILA MEET?

604
01:03:10,018 --> 01:03:12,136
WE MET AT THE NAIL SALON,

605
01:03:12,137 --> 01:03:15,222
- CAN YOU BELIEVE?
- YEAH, I CAN.

606
01:03:15,223 --> 01:03:18,909
LILA WAS SO NICE.
WELL, HERE WE ARE.

607
01:03:18,910 --> 01:03:21,429
- (doorbell rings)
- OH, I SHOULD GET THAT.

608
01:03:21,430 --> 01:03:24,966
- DAVID, CAN YOU POUR THEM
SOME WINE, PLEASE?
- OF COURSE.

609
01:03:31,673 --> 01:03:34,842
- OH, HI!
- HEY, LILA.
GOOD TO SEE YOU.

610
01:03:34,843 --> 01:03:37,778
- AND YOU MUST BE BETHANY.
- YES. HI.

611
01:03:37,779 --> 01:03:39,347
NICE TO MEET YOU.

612
01:03:39,348 --> 01:03:41,815
COME ON IN.

613
01:03:43,952 --> 01:03:45,552
Lauren:
DAVID, THIS FOOD
IS INCREDIBLE.

614
01:03:45,553 --> 01:03:47,071
YOU HAVE TO SHARE
THE RECIPE.

615
01:03:47,072 --> 01:03:49,090
DAVID IS AN
AMAZING COOK, ISN'T HE?

616
01:03:49,091 --> 01:03:51,893
- EXCELLENT.
- DAVE, MAYBE YOU SHOULD
OPEN A RESTAURANT.

617
01:03:51,894 --> 01:03:53,627
(giggles)

618
01:03:53,628 --> 01:03:55,663
I'M SORRY.
I SHOULDN'T LAUGH.

619
01:03:55,664 --> 01:03:57,364
I JUST CAN'T SEE
YOU DOING THAT.

620
01:03:57,365 --> 01:03:59,834
HE LIKES TO WORK
FROM HOME.

621
01:04:01,804 --> 01:04:03,337
WHAT KIND OF WORK
DO YOU DO, DAVID?

622
01:04:03,338 --> 01:04:05,540
HE'S A WRITER.

623
01:04:05,541 --> 01:04:07,441
OH YEAH?
WHAT KIND OF STUFF
DO YOU WRITE?

624
01:04:07,442 --> 01:04:10,278
Lila:
OH, COME ON.
DON'T BE SO SHY.

625
01:04:10,279 --> 01:04:13,281
- IT'S REALLY JUST A HOBBY.
- HE'S WRITING A
CHILDREN'S BOOK.

626
01:04:13,282 --> 01:04:16,116
REALLY?
THAT'S WONDERFUL.
WHAT'S IT ABOUT?

627
01:04:16,117 --> 01:04:19,053
- IT'S ABOUT TWO LITTLE CHILDREN
LIVING IN THE WOODS.
- LILA.

628
01:04:19,054 --> 01:04:21,539
ONE DAY A CREATURE COMES

629
01:04:21,540 --> 01:04:24,909
AND TELLS THEM ABOUT
THIS MAGICAL PLACE JUST
OUTSIDE OF THE FOREST

630
01:04:24,910 --> 01:04:27,511
THAT HAS EVERYTHING
THEY COULD EVER DESIRE.

631
01:04:27,512 --> 01:04:29,546
HE TELLS THEM THAT
HE'LL TAKE THEM THERE

632
01:04:29,547 --> 01:04:33,133
ON ONE CONDITION:
THAT THEY CAN NEVER
GO BACK TO THEIR HOME.

633
01:04:33,134 --> 01:04:37,405
SO THE CHILDREN FOLLOW
THE CREATURE ALL THE WAY
DEEP INTO THE WOODS,

634
01:04:37,406 --> 01:04:40,141
BUT HE'S RUNNING
SO FAST THAT THEY
CAN'T KEEP UP.

635
01:04:40,142 --> 01:04:42,809
HE LEAVES THEM
LOST AND ALL ALONE.

636
01:04:46,731 --> 01:04:48,716
I ASKED YOU
NOT TO TELL IT.

637
01:04:48,717 --> 01:04:52,753
BUT IT'S SO GOOD.
YOU SHOULDN'T BE ASHAMED.

638
01:05:00,195 --> 01:05:03,380
DAVID.  DAVID?

639
01:05:04,933 --> 01:05:08,603
DAVID.
IS THAT HOW IT ENDS, DAVID?

640
01:05:10,772 --> 01:05:12,506
IS IT?

641
01:05:12,507 --> 01:05:17,178
THEY CAN'T EXACTLY
FALL IN LOVE BECAUSE
THEY'RE BROTHER AND SISTER.

642
01:05:17,179 --> 01:05:19,063
THAT IS WHAT YOU WROTE, HM?

643
01:05:25,237 --> 01:05:27,238
TWINS?

644
01:05:33,412 --> 01:05:36,380
OH, NONE FOR ME, THANKS.
I'M DRIVING.

645
01:05:36,381 --> 01:05:38,949
MAYBE ONCE I GET TO KNOW
THE CITY A LITTLE BIT BETTER.

646
01:05:41,620 --> 01:05:43,938
EXCUSE ME.
I HAVE TO CHECK
ON MY FIANCÉE.

647
01:05:46,708 --> 01:05:48,742
(women giggling)

648
01:05:48,743 --> 01:05:50,778
HONEY, IT'S GETTING
A LITTLE BIT LATE.

649
01:05:50,779 --> 01:05:52,396
MAYBE WE SHOULD
HEAD HOME?

650
01:05:52,397 --> 01:05:53,914
OH, HONEY,
I'M HAVIN' FUN.

651
01:05:53,915 --> 01:05:55,950
(laughs)

652
01:05:55,951 --> 01:05:57,785
SEE?  SHE DOESN'T
WANT TO LEAVE.

653
01:05:57,786 --> 01:06:00,370
I KNOW, I KNOW.
I'M A PARTY POOPER.

654
01:06:00,371 --> 01:06:03,024
UNFORTUNATELY,
I'M ON CALL TOMORROW.

655
01:06:03,025 --> 01:06:05,159
UH, IT WAS
A LOVELY EVENING.

656
01:06:05,160 --> 01:06:07,077
- (door opens)
- THANKS FOR HAVING US.

657
01:06:07,078 --> 01:06:09,113
GOOD NIGHT.

658
01:06:09,114 --> 01:06:11,232
(door closes)

659
01:06:11,233 --> 01:06:14,202
Lila:
DAVID, COULD YOU POUR
SOME MORE WINE, PLEASE?

660
01:06:16,888 --> 01:06:18,905
THANK YOU, DAVID.

661
01:06:18,906 --> 01:06:21,125
NOW CAN YOU GO PUT ON
SOME MUSIC, PLEASE?

662
01:06:27,383 --> 01:06:29,283
AH, THANK YOU.

663
01:06:37,175 --> 01:06:39,093
('80s music playing)

664
01:06:44,015 --> 01:06:47,285
WHAT WAS HER PROBLEM?
WASN'T EVERYTHING PERFECT?

665
01:06:47,286 --> 01:06:49,170
IT WAS.

666
01:06:49,171 --> 01:06:51,972
EVERYTHING WAS PERFECT.

667
01:06:51,973 --> 01:06:55,209
THANK YOU.

668
01:06:58,647 --> 01:07:00,415
(giggles)

669
01:07:04,085 --> 01:07:07,354
¶ Well, I thought
I heard you say ¶

670
01:07:07,355 --> 01:07:09,707
¶ And I know
I feel the rain... ¶

671
01:07:09,708 --> 01:07:11,442
(glass clinks)

672
01:07:11,443 --> 01:07:13,744
¶ But I can't
give up looks ¶

673
01:07:13,745 --> 01:07:16,247
¶ Until it's away ¶

674
01:07:18,550 --> 01:07:21,468
¶ Now I just
can't take ¶

675
01:07:21,469 --> 01:07:24,839
¶ The way to live
my life ¶

676
01:07:24,840 --> 01:07:29,410
¶ Holding dear
my last breath in my lungs ¶

677
01:07:31,279 --> 01:07:34,532
¶ I know
i'll see you again ¶

678
01:07:34,533 --> 01:07:36,667
¶ See you again ¶

679
01:07:45,811 --> 01:07:49,297
¶ Don't take my hand
'cause I take it away ¶

680
01:07:52,567 --> 01:07:56,404
¶ And I take everything
just to take it away ¶

681
01:07:58,573 --> 01:08:03,210
¶ Well, you can't
give me problems ¶

682
01:08:03,211 --> 01:08:05,680
¶ You can't
give me signs ¶

683
01:08:05,681 --> 01:08:10,100
¶ As easy as you give,
I can take it away ¶

684
01:08:13,054 --> 01:08:15,973
¶ Now I know
the things I say ¶

685
01:08:15,974 --> 01:08:19,609
¶ Don't hold up
in the rain ¶

686
01:08:19,610 --> 01:08:24,281
¶ Every touch was a gift
straight from my heart... ¶

687
01:08:24,282 --> 01:08:26,183
(music fades)

688
01:08:33,542 --> 01:08:35,142
- (screaming)
- (slicing, thudding)

689
01:08:36,444 --> 01:08:38,462
- (screaming stops)
- (body thuds)

690
01:08:47,138 --> 01:08:48,706
(sighs)
ARE YOU ALMOST FINISHED?

691
01:08:48,707 --> 01:08:50,374
ALMOST.

692
01:08:50,375 --> 01:08:52,276
IT DOESN'T HAVE
TO BE PERFECT.

693
01:08:52,277 --> 01:08:53,611
YES, IT DOES.

694
01:08:54,963 --> 01:08:57,230
DAVID, WE HAVE
TO LEAVE TOMORROW.

695
01:08:58,916 --> 01:09:01,569
I WAS THINKING
MAYBE WE DON'T HAVE
TO LEAVE RIGHT AWAY.

696
01:09:01,570 --> 01:09:03,921
WHAT?

697
01:09:06,007 --> 01:09:07,924
WE'VE BEEN CAREFUL.

698
01:09:07,925 --> 01:09:09,993
MAYBE WE CAN
STAY LONGER.

699
01:09:09,994 --> 01:09:11,979
(laughs)
YOU KNOW WE CAN'T DO THAT.

700
01:09:14,816 --> 01:09:17,802
IF IT'S TOO RISKY,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO STAY.

701
01:09:19,871 --> 01:09:22,306
DAVID, WHERE IS THIS
COMING FROM?

702
01:09:22,307 --> 01:09:23,908
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT?

703
01:09:23,909 --> 01:09:25,475
REALLY?

704
01:09:27,012 --> 01:09:29,496
JUST, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT WE'RE DOING.

705
01:09:33,501 --> 01:09:36,087
YOU CAME
BACK TO ME TONIGHT.

706
01:09:36,088 --> 01:09:37,938
I SAW IT.

707
01:09:40,208 --> 01:09:42,142
YOU CAN COME UPSTAIRS
IF YOU WANT TO.

708
01:09:44,996 --> 01:09:46,914
WE CAN WATCH THE VIDEO.

709
01:09:56,324 --> 01:09:58,509
(water splashes)

710
01:10:32,310 --> 01:10:34,228
(weeping)

711
01:10:53,982 --> 01:10:56,083
(sighs)

712
01:10:59,320 --> 01:11:01,254
(shivering)

713
01:11:29,818 --> 01:11:32,052
WHAT TIME IS IT?

714
01:11:37,174 --> 01:11:39,342
IT'S EARLY.

715
01:11:54,643 --> 01:11:57,277
(sighs)
DAVID, WILL YOU
GO TO THE STORE?

716
01:11:57,278 --> 01:11:59,146
WE'RE OUT OF MILK.

717
01:12:02,150 --> 01:12:03,784
DAVID.

718
01:12:03,785 --> 01:12:07,321
DID YOU HEAR ME?

719
01:12:07,322 --> 01:12:10,374
WE RAN OUT OF MILK
AND I NEED SOME
FOR MY COFFEE.

720
01:12:10,375 --> 01:12:12,676
OKAY.
I'LL GO TO THE STORE.

721
01:12:14,879 --> 01:12:16,913
I'M GONNA PACK.

722
01:12:16,914 --> 01:12:19,349
DO YOU WANT ME TO MAKE
SANDWICHES FOR THE ROAD?

723
01:12:19,350 --> 01:12:21,635
THAT'D BE NICE.

724
01:12:51,048 --> 01:12:53,768
- (scraping)
- (grunting)

725
01:12:57,272 --> 01:12:59,273
(panting)

726
01:13:00,341 --> 01:13:03,160
(knife clatters)

727
01:13:17,742 --> 01:13:19,643
(humming)

728
01:14:31,533 --> 01:14:34,652
(Josh's voice
on film)

729
01:14:34,653 --> 01:14:36,954
Alice on film:
YOU'RE A DORK.

730
01:14:44,762 --> 01:14:46,830
(conversation
on film continues)

731
01:15:01,229 --> 01:15:03,163
(flies buzzing)

732
01:15:47,575 --> 01:15:49,576
HELLO?

733
01:15:50,762 --> 01:15:52,428
ALICE?

734
01:16:03,892 --> 01:16:05,525
YOU BITCH!

735
01:16:05,526 --> 01:16:07,461
(Lila grunting)

736
01:16:27,181 --> 01:16:29,115
(Alice panting)

737
01:16:57,062 --> 01:17:00,664
(spits)

738
01:17:00,665 --> 01:17:02,783
(loud thud)

739
01:17:13,945 --> 01:17:15,963
(breathing heavily)

740
01:17:19,533 --> 01:17:22,269
(footsteps)

741
01:17:22,270 --> 01:17:24,004
OH JESUS.

742
01:17:24,005 --> 01:17:25,405
Oscar: ALICE?

743
01:17:25,406 --> 01:17:27,691
OH MY GOD.

744
01:17:27,692 --> 01:17:32,162
(stammering)
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

745
01:17:32,163 --> 01:17:34,631
- WHO'S COMING?
- HE'S COMING BACK.
JUST GET ME OUT.

746
01:17:34,632 --> 01:17:36,666
JUST GET ME OUT!

747
01:17:36,667 --> 01:17:38,835
(stammering)
WHERE ARE THE KEYS?

748
01:17:38,836 --> 01:17:41,171
I DON'T KNOW.
GO IN THE GARAGE
AND GET SOME TOOLS.

749
01:17:41,172 --> 01:17:43,373
WAIT. THERE'S NO--
(stammering)

750
01:17:43,374 --> 01:17:45,742
GET THE TOOLBOX!
HE'S COMING!

751
01:17:45,743 --> 01:17:47,711
WHO'S COMING?!

752
01:17:51,216 --> 01:17:53,100
(rummaging loudly)

753
01:17:55,803 --> 01:17:57,770
JUST HOLD THE CHAIN.

754
01:18:03,144 --> 01:18:05,178
ALICE, I'M GONNA
CALL THE POLICE, OKAY?

755
01:18:05,179 --> 01:18:07,580
I'M GONNA GO UPSTAIRS
AND CALL THE POLICE.
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

756
01:18:07,581 --> 01:18:09,816
- COME BACK FOR ME.
- I WILL!  I'LL BE
RIGHT BACK.

757
01:18:10,918 --> 01:18:12,852
(rapid footsteps)

758
01:18:17,425 --> 01:18:19,393
(gasping)

759
01:18:23,514 --> 01:18:24,981
(phone beeps)

760
01:18:24,982 --> 01:18:27,183
9-1-1.
What is your emergency?

761
01:18:31,256 --> 01:18:33,473
JUST NEED--
YOU NEED TO HURRY.
I CAN'T GET HER OUT!

762
01:18:33,474 --> 01:18:35,575
(Oscar cries out,
gurgles)

763
01:18:43,251 --> 01:18:45,969
Sir, are you there?
Sir? The police are
on their way.

764
01:18:45,970 --> 01:18:47,570
(rapid footsteps)

765
01:19:00,617 --> 01:19:01,952
ALICE!

766
01:19:01,953 --> 01:19:03,754
STAY BACK, DAVID,
OR I SWEAR I'LL KILL HER.

767
01:19:03,755 --> 01:19:06,973
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
- I'LL CUT HER GODDAMN THROAT!

768
01:19:12,013 --> 01:19:14,231
THROW ME THE KEYS, DAVID.

769
01:19:18,102 --> 01:19:21,771
THROW ME
THE FUCKING KEYS, DAVID!

770
01:19:24,575 --> 01:19:26,676
I'M GONNA KILL HER, DAVID.

771
01:19:26,677 --> 01:19:28,478
I'M GONNA SLIT
HER FUCKIN' THROAT.

772
01:19:35,469 --> 01:19:38,488
IF YOU KILL HER,
WE CAN GO.

773
01:19:45,179 --> 01:19:47,647
DID YOU HEAR WHAT I SAID?
I SAID I'LL KILL HER.

774
01:19:53,754 --> 01:19:56,206
IT'S OKAY.

775
01:20:00,344 --> 01:20:02,512
THIS IS THE ONLY WAY
WE'LL BE TOGETHER.

776
01:20:07,018 --> 01:20:08,785
HERE.

777
01:20:13,958 --> 01:20:17,160
JUST CUT.
I'LL SHOW YOU.

778
01:20:26,537 --> 01:20:29,706
GOODBYE, LILA.

779
01:20:29,707 --> 01:20:31,808
DAVID?

780
01:20:34,028 --> 01:20:36,129
- (Alice cries out)
- ALICE!

781
01:20:39,767 --> 01:20:42,352
- ALICE.
- (gasping)

