(gasping, wheezing)

783
01:21:32,503 --> 01:21:34,838
(coughing)

784
01:21:35,906 --> 01:21:37,941
WHAT'D YOU THINK, DAVID?

785
01:21:37,942 --> 01:21:40,693
THAT SHE REALLY LOVED YOU?

786
01:21:46,300 --> 01:21:49,402
NO ONE'LL EVER
LOVE YOU EXCEPT ME.

787
01:21:56,961 --> 01:21:59,796
WE HAVE TO GO NOW,
DAVID.

788
01:22:02,500 --> 01:22:04,084
COME ON.
WE NEED TO GO.

789
01:22:11,426 --> 01:22:13,159
(garage door whirring)

790
01:22:20,685 --> 01:22:22,686
(police sirens
blaring)

791
01:22:43,458 --> 01:22:45,341
(gasping)

792
01:23:11,669 --> 01:23:14,621
IT WAS BUILT IN 1952--
SO MID-CENTURY MODERN.

793
01:23:14,622 --> 01:23:17,157
THESE WINDOWS
ARE ALL ORIGINAL

794
01:23:17,158 --> 01:23:20,343
AND THEY REALLY DO ALLOW
THE HOUSE JUST TO BE
FILLED WITH LIGHT.

795
01:23:22,679 --> 01:23:25,081
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?

796
01:23:29,253 --> 01:23:31,538
I LOVE IT.
IT'S HOME.

